msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (_pācittiya_)"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:0.4"
msgid "Ovādavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 27"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:0.5"
msgid "27. Saṃvidhānasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on appointments"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:0.6"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-cs-bu-pc27.1, pts-vp-en.2.288, ms2V_589
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjanti."
msgstr "At that time the monks from the group of six traveled on a main road by appointment with nuns."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:1.3"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:1.4"
msgid "“yatheva mayaṃ sapajāpatikā āhiṇḍāma, evamevime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya āhiṇḍantī”ti."
msgstr "“Just as we walk about with our wives, so these Sakyan ascetics walk about by appointment with nuns.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms2V_590
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:1.5"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:1.6"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:1.7"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:1.8"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjissantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can the monks from the group of six travel on a main road by appointment with nuns?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:1.9"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjathā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:1.10"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:1.11"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:1.12"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjissatha."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you travel on a main road by appointment with nuns?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:1.13"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:1.14"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha."
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:1.14a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. HTML: </h3><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc3, ms2V_591
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:1.15"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjeyya, antamaso gāmantarampi, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk travels on a main road by appointment with a nun, even if just between villages, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc4, ms2V_592
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:1.16"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc5, pts-vp-pli4.63, pts-cs-bu-pc27.2, ms2V_593, pts-vp-en.2.289
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū ca bhikkhuniyo ca sāketā sāvatthiṃ addhānamaggappaṭipannā honti."
msgstr "Soon afterwards a number of monks and nuns were traveling from Sāketa to Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:2.2"
msgid "Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo te bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "The nuns said to the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:2.3"
msgid "“mayampi ayyehi saddhiṃ gamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“We’ll go with you.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:2.4"
msgid "“Na, bhaginī, kappati bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjituṃ."
msgstr "“Sisters, it’s not allowable for us to travel on a main road by appointment with nuns."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:2.5"
msgid "Tumhe vā paṭhamaṃ gacchatha mayaṃ vā gamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "You should go first, or we will.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:2.6"
msgid "“Ayyā, bhante, aggapurisā."
msgstr "“Venerables, you have the highest status."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:2.7"
msgid "Ayyāva paṭhamaṃ gacchantū”ti."
msgstr "Please go first.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:2.8"
msgid "Atha kho tāsaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ pacchā gacchantīnaṃ antarāmagge corā acchindiṃsu ca dūsesuñca."
msgstr "But because the nuns went behind, they were robbed and raped by bandits."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:2.9"
msgid "Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo sāvatthiṃ gantvā bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "When they arrived at Sāvatthī, they told the nuns there what had happened."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:2.10"
msgid "Bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "The nuns then told the monks,"

#. REF: ms2V_594
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:2.11"
msgid "Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "who in turn told the Master."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:2.12"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

#. HTML: <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:2.13"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, satthagamanīye magge sāsaṅkasammate sappaṭibhaye bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjituṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to travel on a main road by appointment with a nun if it’s a dangerous and frightening road that should be traveled with a group."

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:2.14"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "”And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:2.14a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc7, ms2V_595
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:2.15"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjeyya, antamaso gāmantarampi, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘If a monk travels on a main road by appointment with a nun, even if just between villages, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

# NOTE: _Sattho_, often translated as caravan. According to [](Sp-ṭ.2.489) this refers either to a caravan of travelers walking on foot or to a caravan of carts: _satthoti jaṅghasattho sakaṭasattho vā_.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:2.16"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo. Satthagamanīyo hoti maggo sāsaṅkasammato sappaṭibhayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr "The appropriate reason is that the road is considered dangerous and frightening and should be traveled with a group.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, pts-cs-bu-pc27.3.1, ms2V_596
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms2V_597
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.1.6"
msgid "Bhikkhunī nāma"
msgstr "A nun:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.1.7"
msgid "ubhatosaṃghe upasampannā."
msgstr "she has been given the full ordination by both Orders."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, ms2V_598
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.1.8"
msgid "Saddhinti"
msgstr "With:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.1.9"
msgid "ekato."
msgstr "together."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc11, pts-vp-en.2.290, ms2V_599
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.1.10"
msgid "Saṃvidhāyāti—"
msgstr "By appointment: if he makes an appointment like this:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.1.11"
msgid "“gacchāma, bhagini, gacchāmāyya; gacchāmāyya, gacchāma, bhagini; ajja vā hiyyo vā pare vā gacchāmā”ti saṃvidahati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he says, “Let’s go, Sister,” and she replies, “Yes, let’s go, Venerable;” or she says, “Let’s go, Venerable,” and he replies, “Yes, let’s go, Sister;” or he says, “Let’s go today/tomorrow/the day after tomorrow,” then he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc12, ms2V_600
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.1.12"
msgid "Antamaso gāmantarampīti"
msgstr "Even if just between villages:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.1.13"
msgid "kukkuṭasampāte gāme, gāmantare gāmantare āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "when the villages are a chicken’s flight apart, then for every village interval he commits an offense entailing confession."

# NOTE: Half a _yojana_. The length of a _yojana_ is uncertain, and perhaps it never was a precise distance. But a reasonable estimate is 8 miles or just under 13 kilometers (see ACMC, p.16). Thus half a _yojana_ is just over 6 km.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.1.14"
msgid "Agāmake araññe, addhayojane addhayojane āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is in an uninhabited area, in the wilderness, then for every six kilometers he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc13, ms2V_601
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.1.15"
msgid "Aññatra samayāti"
msgstr "Unless there is an appropriate reason:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.1.16"
msgid "ṭhapetvā samayaṃ."
msgstr "except at an appropriate time."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc14, ms2V_602
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.1.17"
msgid "Satthagamanīyo nāma"
msgstr "The road […] should be traveled with a group:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.1.18"
msgid "maggo na sakkā hoti vinā satthena gantuṃ."
msgstr "it is not possible to travel without a group."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc15, ms2V_603
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.1.19"
msgid "Sāsaṅkaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Dangerous:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
#. VAR: tasmiṃ magge → yasmiṃ magge (?)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.1.20"
msgid "tasmiṃ magge corānaṃ niviṭṭhokāso dissati, bhuttokāso dissati, ṭhitokāso dissati, nisinnokāso dissati, nipannokāso dissati."
msgstr "thieves have been seen along that road, camped, eating, standing, seated, or lying down."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc16, pts-vp-pli4.64, ms2V_604
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.1.21"
msgid "Sappaṭibhayaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Frightening:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.1.22"
msgid "tasmiṃ magge corehi manussā hatā dissanti, viluttā dissanti, ākoṭitā dissanti, sappaṭibhayaṃ gantvā appaṭibhayaṃ dassetvā uyyojetabbā—"
msgstr "thieves have been seen along that road, injuring, robbing, or beating people. If they go thinking it is frightening, but then see that it is not, the nuns are to be dismissed,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.1.23"
msgid "“gacchatha, bhaginiyo”ti."
msgstr "“Go, Sisters.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc17, pts-cs-bu-pc27.3.2, pts-vp-en.2.291, ms2V_605
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.2.1"
msgid "Saṃvidahite saṃvidahitasaññī ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjati, antamaso gāmantarampi, aññatra samayā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If there is an appointment, and he perceives that there is, and he travels on a main road with a nun, even if just between villages, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.2.2"
msgid "Saṃvidahite vematiko ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjati, antamaso gāmantarampi, aññatra samayā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If there is an appointment, but he is unsure if there is, and he travels on a main road with a nun, even if just between villages, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.2.3"
msgid "Saṃvidahite, asaṃvidahitasaññī ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjati, antamaso gāmantarampi, aññatra samayā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If there is an appointment, but he perceives that there is not, and he travels on a main road with a nun, even if just between villages, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc18, ms2V_606
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.2.4"
msgid "Bhikkhu saṃvidahati bhikkhunī na saṃvidahati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If the monk makes an appointment, but the nun does not express her agreement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.2.5"
msgid "Asaṃvidahite saṃvidahitasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If there is no appointment, but he perceives that there is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.2.6"
msgid "Asaṃvidahite vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If there is no appointment, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.2.7"
msgid "Asaṃvidahite asaṃvidahitasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If there is no appointment, and he perceives that there is not, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc19, pts-cs-bu-pc27.3.3, ms2V_607
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.3.2"
msgid "samaye,"
msgstr "if there is an appropriate reason;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.3.3"
msgid "asaṃvidahitvā gacchati,"
msgstr "if he goes without an appointment;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.3.4"
msgid "bhikkhunī saṃvidahati, bhikkhu na saṃvidahati,"
msgstr "if the nun has made an appointment, but he has not expressed his agreement;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.3.5"
msgid "visaṅketena gacchanti,"
msgstr "if they go, but not according to the appointment;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.3.6"
msgid "āpadāsu,"
msgstr "if there are dangers;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.3.7"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.3.8"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc20, ms2V_608
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:3.3.9"
msgid "Saṃvidhānasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ."
msgstr "The seventh rule, the training rule on appointments, is finished."
